https://leetcode.com/problems/sliding-window-maximum/description/

class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> maxSlidingWindow(vector<int>& nums, int k) 
    {
        vector<int> res;
        deque<int> dq;
        int n=nums.size();

        for(int i=0;i<k;i++)
        {
            while(!dq.empty() && nums[i]>=nums[dq.back()])
            {
                dq.pop_back();
            }
            dq.push_back(i); //add idx not value
        }
        //add 1st window ans to res
        res.push_back(nums[dq.front()]); //front always is answer

        for(int i=k;i<n;i++)
        {
            //check if index in queue is part of curr window
            while(!dq.empty() && dq.front()<=i-k)
            {
                dq.pop_front();
            }
            while(!dq.empty() && nums[i]>=nums[dq.back()])
            {
                dq.pop_back();
            }
            dq.push_back(i);
            res.push_back(nums[dq.front()]);
        }
        return res;
    }
};

Maximum Sliding Window – Monotonic Deque Approach

Maintain a deque dq (stores indices, not values).
Deque is maintained in decreasing order of values.

Traverse array using one pointer i.

At each step:
• Remove indices from front if they are out of window (dq.front() <= i - k).
• Remove elements from back while nums[i] >= nums[dq.back()] (useless elements).
• Add current index i to deque.
• When window size ≥ k:
o The front of deque gives max → nums[dq.front()]
o Add it to result

Key Idea
Keep only useful candidates for maximum in deque (in decreasing order).

Important Trick
Remove all smaller elements from back because they can never become max in future.

Why index not value?
To check if element is out of window (i - k condition) and handle duplicates.

Time: O(N)
(each element added & removed at most once)

Space: O(K)
